author: mattmann
msg: - OODT-310 and OODT-215: Generic WorkflowState class. Unlike the wengine-branch, this is *not* an abstract class, intended to be inherited from and to statically type and define workflow states. Instead, it's a simple POJO container, configured by WorkflowLifeCycle to dynamically represent workflow state in a configurable way.

author: gstein
msg: Eliminate massive amounts of now-used code. This module now fears me.
* subversion/libsvn_delta/compat.c:
(enum action_code_t): killed, with extreme prejudice
(struct operation): reduced to a mewling form of its original self
(get_operation): vaporized in a blink of an eye
(build): tossed into the stinking pits of hellfire
(add_directory_cb): forever silenced its call to build()
(add_file_cb): removed its untoward association with build()
(add_symlink_cb): it is now crying over losing its call to build()
(add_absent_cb): carved the build() call from its flesh
(alter_directory_cb): chewed its build() call, and spit it out
(alter_file_cb): oh, boo hoo. build() removed. deal with it.
(delete_cb): kicked the build() right out of it.
(copy_cb): with an evil cackle, nuked its build() call
(move_cb): stomped its build() call into reddish mush
(change_props): nuked from orbit
(drive_tree): fed to the slavering wolf-beast
(drive_root): glassed in nuclear fire
(complete_cb): precision scalpel wound to remove drive_root() call
(abort_cb): sniper fired the drive_root() call into giblets
(do_unlock): shoved its operation handling down the disposal
(svn_delta__editor_from_delta): mangled its root operation setup
